[21:26] <patrickb> re "Why are we offering a ZIP and an MSI if they are the same size?" - MSI is an installer that sets everything (including the PATHs) up. Use this unless you know better. The ZIP is simply a zipped up relocatable Rakudo. Suitable for building your own Raku programs on top and distributing them.

[21:32] <patrickb> re "The MSI isn't signed." Yes this sucks big time. I've invested countless hours and more than one and a half years in total trying to get this sorted out with the YAS guys. When we finally got to the point where we were ready to order a cert, the idea of a separate Raku foundation came up and all plans of ordering a Cert via YAS were moot. In the meantime SignPath started offering certs for OSS 

[21:32] <patrickb> for free. So only need to find the time to get it going with them or do it via the to not yet established new Raku Foundation once it exists.

